The paper deals with convex optimization, machine learning, and data mining, which are all topics that fall under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on clustering and optimization on graphs, which falls under the category of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses distributed and scalable algorithms, which are relevant to the category of "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of non-convex optimization, which is relevant to the category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with event detection in time series data, which is relevant to the category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
